# Browser automation (Playwright / cursor-ide-browser)

When using browser tools (Playwright MCP or cursor-ide-browser):

- **Headless** — Use for documentation research, simple page fetches, and scraping. No login or session needed.
- **Remote debugging** — Use when logging into an account (e.g. X/Twitter, GitHub) or when the site depends on cookies/session. Prefer remote debugging for login flows and authenticated actions.

Do not use remote debugging for read-only documentation tasks; use headless instead.
